{"blocks":[{"key":"4o5r3","text":"Remove genes showing BLASTP (blast-2.2.26) hits to transposon proteins in the UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot database (v2019_11), or with more than 70% of their coding regions overlapping repetitive sequences from the combined gene set.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"5k1ji","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3fsgi","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"88mg8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"7ftpd","text":"Use the parameters \"-F F -e 1e-5\" when running BLASTP.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6s749","text":"Finally, perform functional annotation by searching the Limnodynastes dumerilii dumerilii proteins against public databases of UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot (v2019_11), NCBI nr (v20191030), and KEGG (v93.0) with BLASTP (blast-2.2.26;).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":56,"length":34}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"f6im7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4jhjp","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"94e3v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1f15i","text":"Use the parameters \"-F F -e 1e -5\" when running BLASTP.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6874d","text":"Download protein sequences of diverse vertebrate species (Danio rerio (Ensembl, release-98), Xenopus tropicalis (Ensembl, release-98), Xenopus laevis (NCBI, GCF_001663975.1), Nanorana parkeri (NCBI, GCF_000935625.1), Microcaecilia unicolor (NCBI, GCF_901765095.1), Rhinatrema bivittatum (NCBI, GCF_901001135.1), Anolis carolinensis (Ensembl, release-98), Gallus gallus (Ensembl, release-98) and Homo sapiens (Ensembl, release-98)).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":58,"length":12},{"style":"italic","offset":92,"length":20},{"style":"italic","offset":135,"length":15},{"style":"italic","offset":175,"length":16},{"style":"italic","offset":217,"length":23},{"style":"italic","offset":265,"length":22},{"style":"italic","offset":312,"length":20},{"style":"italic","offset":355,"length":14},{"style":"italic","offset":395,"length":13}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eqkdj","text":"Align the protein sequences from the previous step to the Limnodynastes dumerilii dumerilii genome assembly by using TBLASTN (blast-2.2.26).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":58,"length":33}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7ebia","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ek85p","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"a376k","text":"Extract the genomic sequences of the candidate loci together with 5 kb flanking sequences. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"dthvs","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7th4v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"fbssk","text":"Align the homologous proteins to the extracted genomics sequences from the previous step by using GeneWise (wise-2.2.0) for exon-intron structure determinations.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"afnb8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"bkrks","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4co6g","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5h624","text":"Randomly pick 1,000 homology-derived gene models of Limnodynastes dumerilii dumerilii  with complete open reading frames (ORFS) and reciprocal aligning rates exceeding 90% against the X. tropicalis proteins to train AUGUSTUS (v3.3.1, RRID:SCR_008417).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":52,"length":33},{"style":"italic","offset":184,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"chjb3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ce69o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"89mue","text":"Use the obtained gene parameters by AUGUSTUS to predict protein-coding genes on the repeat-masked Limnodynastes dumerilii dumerilii genome assembly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":98,"length":34}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
